  "stimulus": "The functions $f$ and $g$ have continuous second derivatives. The table gives values of the functions and their derivatives at selected values of $x$.\n\n| $x$ | $f(x)$ | $f'(x)$ | $g(x)$ | $g'(x)$ |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | $-6$ | 3 | 2 | 8 |\n| 2 | 2 | $-2$ | $-3$ | 0 |\n| 3 | 8 | 7 | 6 | 2 |\n| 6 | 4 | 5 | 3 | $-1$ |",
  "stimulus_image": null,
  "documents": null,
  "parts": [
    {
      "letter": "a",
      "prompt": "Let $k(x) = f(g(x))$. Write an equation for the line tangent to the graph of $k$ at $x = 3$.",
      "point_value": 3,
      "scoring_notes": "From scoring key: $k(3) = f(g(3)) = f(6) = 4$. $k'(3) = f'(6) \\cdot g'(3) = 5 \\cdot 2 = 10$. Tangent line: $y = 4 + 10(x-3)$.",
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "a1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "$k(3) = f(g(3)) = f(6) = 4$ and $k'(3) = f'(g(3)) \\cdot g'(3) = f'(6) \\cdot g'(3)$",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "$k(3) = f(g(3)) = f(6) = 4$",
                "$k'(3) = f'(g(3)) \\cdot g'(3) = f'(6) \\cdot g'(3)$"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "a2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct slope",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Correct slope"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$k'(3) = f'(6) \\cdot 2 = 5 \\cdot 2 = 10$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "a3",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Tangent line equation",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Tangent line equation"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$y = 4 + 10(x - 3)$ or equivalent"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "letter": "b",
      "prompt": "Let $h(x) = \\frac{g(x)}{f(x)}$. Find $h'(1)$.",
      "point_value": 3,
      "scoring_notes": "From scoring key: $h'(1) = \\frac{(-6)(8) - (2)(3)}{36} = \\frac{-54}{36} = -\\frac{3}{2}$.",
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "b1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Applies quotient rule",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Applies quotient rule"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$h'(x) = \\frac{f(x) \\cdot g'(x) - g(x) \\cdot f'(x)}{[f(x)]^2}$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "b2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct expression",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Correct expression"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$h'(1) = \\frac{f(1) \\cdot g'(1) - g(1) \\cdot f'(1)}{[f(1)]^2} = \\frac{(-6)(8) - (2)(3)}{(-6)^2}$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "b3",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct answer",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Correct answer"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$h'(1) = \\frac{-48 - 6}{36} = \\frac{-54}{36} = -\\frac{3}{2}$"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
